# 📌 Technical Architecture & Code Guidelines

## 🔍 Project Purpose

This monorepo application is designed to serve as a listing platform that will scale across multiple business categories and geographic zones (e.g., provinces and cities). The application prioritizes **discoverability and SEO**, serving server-rendered or statically generated content whenever possible.

Our tech stack is designed to maximize performance, maintainability, and scalability.

## 🧱 Tech Stack Overview

- **Monorepo**: Managed with [Turborepo](mdc:https:/turbo.build/repo)
- **Package Manager**: [pnpm](mdc:https:/pnpm.io)
- **Framework**: [Next.js 15 (App Router)](mdc:https:/nextjs.org/docs)
- **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS v3](mdc:https:/tailwindcss.com) with [shadcn/ui](mdc:https:/ui.shadcn.com)
- **ORM**: [Prisma](mdc:https:/www.prisma.io)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL
- **Rendering Strategy**:
  - Prefer **SSG (Static Site Generation)** for most listings and pages
  - Use **SSR (Server Side Rendering)** for dynamic SEO-critical pages
- **Scrapers**: Custom-built scrapers will populate the database and keep it updated regularly.

> ⚠️ Before adding a new library or abstraction, validate its necessity within the SSR/SSG-first architecture model. We aim to keep client-side logic minimal.

