## 📁 Folder Structure Convention

Each app should follow a modular structure and respect the monorepo workspace separation:
```bash
apps/
└── mechanic-finder/           # Main Next.js 15 app
    ├── app/                   # App Router pages
    │   ├── (public)/          # Public pages like home, contact, etc. (optional)
    │   │   ├── page.tsx       # Main landing page
    │   │   └── contact/
    │   │       └── page.tsx
    │   │
    │   ├── [city]/[category]/ # Dynamic listing pages by city and category
    │   │   └── page.tsx
    │   │
    │   └── layout.tsx         # Root layout for the app
    │
    ├── components/            # Reusable project components
    ├── lib/                   # Utility functions, validators, etc.
    ├── prisma/                # Prisma client, middlewares, seeders
    ├── styles/                # Global styles
    ├── i18n/                  # Translation files (es, en, etc.)
    └── middleware.ts          # Middleware for redirects, auth, etc.
└── other-app-finder           # Another Next.js 15 app
packages/
├── ui/                        # Shared UI components and utils (based on shadcn/ui)
    ├── components/    #export
        ├── Button/ #(example)
          ├── Button.tsx
          ├── types.ts
          ├── index.ts
        ├── Command/ #(example)
          ├── command.tsx
          ├── index.ts
        ├── index.ts
    ├── ads/ #export
    ├── utils/ #export
    ├── lib/
    ├── styles/
├── types/                     # Shared TypeScript types
├── config/                    # Shared config (eslint, tailwind, tsconfig)
└── scraper/                   # Scrapers for seeding and updating listings
└── db/
    └── prisma/
          └── schema.prisma
    └── client.ts
    └── index.ts
```

> ✅ Reuse components from `packages/ui` whenever possible. If a component is tied to a domain or layout section, place it in `components/`.
- We use shadcn components.
